<br>
BTW, don't forget to bring a timer.  I use BigClock on my Palm m500.  It has 2 timers with big letters.  In the North Yeti cave I set one for 16:00 and the other for 20:00.  Whenever I kill the wanderer I start the 16.  When I kill the static in the hallway I start the 20.  I don't want anybody joining in when I least expect it.<br>
<br>
In the South Yeti cave I have both timers at 16:00.  One for each wanderer.  Much much easier.<br>
<br>
Izarek<br>
43rd Magician of Tunare<br>
Tarew Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uizarek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izarek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(11/15/01 10:36:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DL Tundra Yeti (FYI)</span><hr size=1> Now that I'm 44 I relized that two blazes is still the best way to go.  Only difference is my pet chews them up so fast that I have to nuke the second his health drops.  Otherwise I don't get two nukes off before he runs, and I'm less likely to get exp.<br>
<br>
